    <pre>Well, Google seems to be not happy with our SSL cert. But now that they're on
the non-SSL feed, they're happy.</pre>
   </td>
  </tr>
 
 
  <tr>
   <th><a href="msg2362">msg2362 (view)</a></th>
   <th>Author: paulproteus</th>
   <th>Date: 2011-08-21.03:05:59</th>
   <th>
    
   </th>
  </tr>
  <tr>
   <td colspan="4" class="content">
    <pre>The problem was that FeedBurner was having trouble with our SSL feed.

I fixed the problem in nginx, as verified by wget locally. Google still seems
not to enjoy feedburning our SSL-based feed, so I changed the FeedBurner
configuration so that it uses the <a href="http://-based">http://-based</a> feed (non-SSL).

I'm not thrilled about that. If our SSL-based site works, Google should be able
to fetch it also.

Therefore I'm marking this in-progress. In a day or two, I'll retry setting
FeedBurner to use SSL, and if that works, I'll mark as truly resolved.</pre>
   </td>
  </tr>
 
 
  <tr>
   <th><a href="msg2361">msg2361 (view)</a></th>
